<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-19300] AsyncConsumer#unsubscribe always timeout due to GroupAuthorizationException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-19300</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;it can be reproduced by GroupAuthorizerIntegrationTest.testConsumeUnsubscribeWithoutGroupPermission.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The root cause is shown below.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. AsyncConsumer#unsubscribe is executed&lt;br/&gt;
2. process(UnsubscribeEvent) changes the state to LEAVING&lt;br/&gt;
3. the state is changed to UNSUBSCRIBED in generating Heartbeat&lt;br/&gt;
4. the `LeaveInProgress` is skipped in transitionToFatal since the state is UNSUBSCRIBED&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The behavior is inconsistent to classic consumer&lt;/p&gt;</description>
